description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Safeguarding Team is looking for a band 3 Administrator, ideally for 37.5 hours per week. This could also suit somebody looking for a secondment opportunity for 12 months in the first instance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is to provide wide ranging administrative support to a team of enthusiastic and forward thinking Named Safeguarding Professionals. The team provides advice and support, training and supervision to all professionals across the whole organisation, whose role includes protecting adults children and their families from harm. They also have responsibility for ensuring the Trust fulfils its statutory safeguarding responsibilities through implementation of local and national guidelines and policy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be able to demonstrate a strong background in administration, effective team working, and possess excellent organisational and interpersonal skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust promotes flexible working options on all appropriate positions and our managers welcome these discussions during the recruitment process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMaggie WardJob titleLead for Safeguarding ChildrenEmail addressMaggie.Ward@swft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
